Share this on WhatsAppSuper Eagles midfielder, Oghenekaro Etebo has joined Galatasaray on a season-long loan from Stoke City.

The 24-year-old who will spend the 2020/21 campaign at the Turkish club, was unveiled on Wednesday, September 9 after undergoing his medicals.

“Galatasaray Sportif A. informed the Public Disclosure Platform that an agreement was reached for the transfer of professional football player Oghenekaro Etebo until the end of the season,” the club revealed on its website.

“We welcome Oghenekaro Etebo to our club and wish him a successful season under the Galatasaray jersey.”
Oghenekaro Etebo

On joining the Turkish side, Etebo told the club’s official website: “I am very happy to come to such a big and historic club. I thank our president and our vice presidents for their warm welcome. I really felt at home. See you at the championship at the end of the season,”

“On this occasion, I would like to thank our President, all technical staff and all our fans for a warm welcome. ”

The move marks his second loan spell away from Stoke City having spent half of last season on loan at LaLiga side Getafe.


				
